## Food Guide: Must-Try Street Food

### Northern Thai Specialties

**Khao Soi** (ข้าวซอย) - 50-70 THB
Curry noodle soup with crispy noodles on top. The signature dish of Chiang Mai.
*Where*: Sunday market has best variety

**Sai Oua** (ไส้อั่ว) - 40 THB
Spicy northern Thai sausage with lemongrass and herbs.
*Tip*: Ask for "not spicy" (ไม่เผ็ด - mâi phèt)

**Nam Prik Num** (น้ำพริกหนุ่ม) - 60 THB
Spicy green chili dip with vegetables and sticky rice.

**Khanom Jeen Nam Ngiaw** (ขนมจีนน้ำเงี้ยว) - 50 THB
Rice noodles with tomato-based pork curry.

### Sweet Treats

**Mango Sticky Rice** (ข้าวเหนียวมะม่วง) - 60-80 THB
*Season*: March-June for best mangoes
*Markets*: All markets, but freshest at JJ Market morning

**Roti** (โรตี) - 30-50 THB
Thai-style pancake with banana, chocolate, or condensed milk.
*Best*: Saturday market roti stall (near South Gate)

**Coconut Ice Cream** (ไอศกรีมกะทิ) - 50 THB
Served in coconut shell with toppings.

### Israeli-Friendly Options

**Vegetarian/Vegan Stalls**:
Look for "เจ" (Jay) symbol = vegan Buddhist food
- Many curries naturally vegan
- Pad Thai without egg/shrimp
- Fresh fruit: 20-40 THB per cup

**Kosher-Style**: No pork or seafood options
- Chicken satay: 40 THB (10 skewers)
- Grilled chicken: 80-120 THB
- Vegetable spring rolls: 30 THB

