## Insider Tips for Israeli Travelers

1. **WhatsApp Groups**: Join "Israelis in Chiang Mai" group for real-time market updates and meet-ups

2. **Hebrew-Speaking Vendors**:
   - Silver shop at Saturday market (owner lived in Israel)
   - Massage stall on Sunday market (knows Hebrew numbers)
   - Food vendor at Night Bazaar (popular with Israelis)

3. **Israeli Products**: Some vendors stock Israeli flags, Star of David jewelry because of demand

4. **Sabbath Alternative**: If you keep Shabbat, visit Friday evening markets or Sunday market ends after Shabbat

5. **Kosher Food**: No kosher food at markets, but Chabad House nearby has kosher meals

6. **Shipping Home**: Some vendors ship to Israel (150-300 THB per kg via Thai Post)

